    <div class="reveal">
      <h2 class="section-title">Do this</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Wait 24 hours before using the surface after refinishing.</li>
        <li>Clean weekly with a mild liquid cleaner and a soft sponge.</li>
        <li>Rinse after use and wipe dry to prevent mineral buildup.</li>
        <li>Use a non-slip mat that is not suction-based.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1.6rem;">
        <strong>Recommended cleaners</strong>
        <p>Gentle dish soap, non-abrasive bathroom cleaner, or acrylic-safe products.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reveal">
      <h2 class="section-title">Avoid this</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Abrasive powders, scouring pads, or steel wool.</li>
        <li>Bleach, ammonia, acids, or harsh drain cleaners.</li>
        <li>Suction-cup bathmats, soap dishes, or organizers.</li>
        <li>Leaving bottles, razors, or metal cans on the surface.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout" style="margin-top:1.6rem;">
        <strong>Need a touch-up?</strong>
        <p>If you notice chips or wear, contact us early for a quick repair.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
